<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,831,1337]" box="[264,387,831,856]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis box="[264,387,831,856]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Comments</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,831,1337]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
In the three phylogenetic studies of the tribe 
<taxonomicName box="[850,1006,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Augochlorini">Augochlorini</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Eickwort" box="[1023,1203,871,897]" pageId="4" pageNumber="30" refString="Eickwort, G. C. (1969) A comparative morphological study and generic revision of the augochlorine bees (Hymenoptera: Halictidae). The University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 48, 325 - 524." type="journal article" year="1969">
Eickwort 
<number box="[1142,1203,871,897]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1969.0">1969</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Danforth" pageId="4" pageNumber="30" refString="Danforth, B. N. &amp; Eickwort, G. C. (1997) The evolution of social behavior in the augochlorine sweat bees (Hymenoptera: Halictidae) based on a phylogenetic analysis of the genera. In Choe, J. C. &amp; Crespi, B. J. (Eds). Social Behavior in Insects and Arachnids. Cambridge University Press, 270 - 292." type="book chapter" year="1997">
Danforth &amp; Eickwort 
<number box="[414,475,911,937]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Engel" box="[491,632,911,937]" pageId="4" pageNumber="30" refString="Engel, M. S. (2000) Classification of the bee tribe Augochlorini (Hymenoptera: Halictidae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural history, 250, 1 - 89." type="journal article" year="2000">
Engel 
<number box="[569,632,911,937]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), the relationships of 
<taxonomicName box="[895,1052,911,936]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Thectochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[895,1052,911,936]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Thectochlora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not consensual. A close relationship of the genus with 
<taxonomicName box="[694,877,951,976]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochloropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[694,877,951,976]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Augochloropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Eickwort 1969" authorityName="Eickwort" authorityYear="1969" box="[936,1318,951,977]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlorodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[936,1113,951,976]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Augochlorodes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Eickwort" box="[1129,1310,951,977]" pageId="4" pageNumber="30" refString="Eickwort, G. C. (1969) A comparative morphological study and generic revision of the augochlorine bees (Hymenoptera: Halictidae). The University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 48, 325 - 524." type="journal article" year="1969">
Eickwort 
<number box="[1247,1310,951,977]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1969.0">1969</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, a basal and isolated position in the tribe (
<bibRefCitation author="Danforth" box="[757,1082,991,1017]" pageId="4" pageNumber="30" refString="Danforth, B. N. &amp; Eickwort, G. C. (1997) The evolution of social behavior in the augochlorine sweat bees (Hymenoptera: Halictidae) based on a phylogenetic analysis of the genera. In Choe, J. C. &amp; Crespi, B. J. (Eds). Social Behavior in Insects and Arachnids. Cambridge University Press, 270 - 292." type="book chapter" year="1997">
Danforth &amp; Eickwort 
<number box="[1022,1082,991,1017]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) or a grouping with 
<taxonomicName box="[264,391,1031,1056]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Megalopta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[264,391,1031,1056]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Megalopta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Engel 2000" authorityName="Engel" authorityYear="2000" box="[460,800,1031,1057]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Ischnomelissa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[460,626,1031,1056]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Ischnomelissa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Engel" box="[648,791,1031,1057]" pageId="4" pageNumber="30" refString="Engel, M. S. (2000) Classification of the bee tribe Augochlorini (Hymenoptera: Halictidae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural history, 250, 1 - 89." type="journal article" year="2000">
Engel 
<number box="[731,791,1031,1057]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
have been proposed. In spite of this, the monophyly of the genus is strongly supported by the dorsal hook on the fore leg trochanter and by the female acarinarium. The latter structure is associated with specialized acarid mites carried by the females (
<bibRefCitation author="Fain" box="[620,817,1151,1177]" pageId="4" pageNumber="30" refString="Fain, A., Engel, M. S., Flecthtmann, C. H. W., and O'Connor, B. M. (1999) A new genus and species of Acaridae (Acari) phoretic on Thectochlora alaris (Hymenoptera: Halictidae: Augochlorini) from South America. International Journal of Acarology, 25, 163 - 172." type="journal article" year="1999">
Fain 
<emphasis box="[684,738,1151,1176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[754,817,1151,1177]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). No variation was found in this character among the species recognized here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,831,1337]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Five species are here recognized in 
<taxonomicName box="[731,887,1231,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Thectochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[731,887,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Thectochlora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Vachal, 1904" authorityName="Vachal" authorityYear="1904" box="[903,1184,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Halictus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alaris">
<emphasis box="[903,1000,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. alaris</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Vachal" box="[1016,1175,1231,1257]" pageId="4" pageNumber="30" refString="Vachal, J. (1904) Etude sur les Halictus d'Amerique. Miscellanea Entomologica, 12, 9 - 24." type="journal article" year="1904">
Vachal, 
<number box="[1113,1175,1231,1257]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1904.0">1904</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Strand, 1910" authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochloropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="basiatra" status="new combination">
<emphasis box="[1196,1323,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. basiatra</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Strand" box="[272,425,1271,1297]" pageId="4" pageNumber="30" refString="Strand, E. (1910) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Hymenopterenfauna von Paraguay. Zoologisches Jahrbuch, Abteilung fur Systematik, 29, 455 - 562." type="journal article" year="1910">
Strand, 
<number box="[365,425,1271,1297]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1910.0">1910</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[442,656,1270,1296]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[442,656,1270,1296]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">new combination</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[671,835,1271,1296]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Thectochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachycera" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[671,835,1271,1296]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. brachycera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[842,987,1270,1296]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[842,987,1270,1296]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1002,1120,1271,1296]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Thectochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamata" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[1002,1120,1271,1296]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. hamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1127,1272,1270,1296]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1127,1272,1270,1296]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[264,359,1311,1336]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Thectochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mixta" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[264,359,1311,1336]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. mixta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[365,509,1310,1336]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[365,509,1310,1336]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
. Their phylogenetic relationships are presented in the 
<figureCitation box="[1146,1263,1311,1337]" captionStart="FIGURE 34" captionStartId="27.[264,367,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[417,1160,1347,1827]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[417,1180,1334,1833]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 34. Cladogram for species of Thectochlora. L = 15; Ci = 93; Ri = 90." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174222/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Figure 
<number box="[1230,1263,1311,1337]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,1391,1657]" box="[264,383,1391,1416]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis box="[264,383,1391,1416]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,1391,1657]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Pronotal dorsal ridge strongly lamellate; fourth male sternum produced laterally into a posterior process with strong setae at apex (
<bibRefCitation author="Moure" box="[814,970,1471,1497]" pageId="4" pageNumber="30" refString="Moure, J. S. (1940) Apoidea neotropica. Revista do Museu Paulista, 2, 39 - 64." type="journal article" year="1940">
Moure 
<number box="[907,970,1471,1497]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1940.0">1940</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); anterior border of the first female tergum modified into a well-developed acarinarium (
<bibRefCitation author="Eickwort" box="[980,1161,1511,1537]" pageId="4" pageNumber="30" refString="Eickwort, G. C. (1969) A comparative morphological study and generic revision of the augochlorine bees (Hymenoptera: Halictidae). The University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 48, 325 - 524." type="journal article" year="1969">
Eickwort 
<number box="[1098,1161,1511,1537]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1969.0">1969</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); dorsal hook on the mid leg trochanter present in both sexes (
<bibRefCitation author="Engel" box="[850,994,1551,1577]" pageId="4" pageNumber="30" refString="Engel, M. S. (2000) Classification of the bee tribe Augochlorini (Hymenoptera: Halictidae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural history, 250, 1 - 89." type="journal article" year="2000">
Engel 
<number box="[930,994,1551,1577]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Other valuable diagnostic features of the genus are the anteriorly projecting mesoscutum, the flattened metasoma, the pectinate inner tibial spur in the female hind leg, and the obtuse epistomal sulcus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
